  "body": "# Description \r\nAs a new user, I want a better error message for `peer generate` so that I know how to generate peer IDs. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Clear error message when `config` directory doesn't exist when using `peer generate` without the `--outputFile` option. \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nRun `artemis peer generate 3` without first creating `config` directory: \r\n\r\nFollowing error is displayed: \r\n```\r\njava.io.FileNotFoundException: ./config/peer-ids.dat (No such file or directory)\r\n\tat java.base/java.io.FileOutputStream.open0(Native Method)\r\n\tat java.base/java.io.FileOutputStream.open(FileOutputStream.java:292)\r\n\tat java.base/java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(FileOutputStream.java:235)\r\n\tat java.base/java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(FileOutputStream.java:124)\r\n\tat java.base/java.io.FileWriter.<init>(FileWriter.java:141)\r\n\tat tech.pegasys.artemis.PeerCommand.generate(PeerCommand.java:60)\r\n\tat java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)\r\n\tat java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(NativeMethodAccessorImpl.java:62)\r\n\tat java.base/jdk.internal.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43)\r\n\tat java.base/java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:567)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine.executeUserObject(CommandLine.java:1762)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine.access$900(CommandLine.java:145)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine$RunLast.handle(CommandLine.java:2101)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine$RunLast.handle(CommandLine.java:2068)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine$AbstractParseResultHandler.execute(CommandLine.java:1935)\r\n\tat picocli.CommandLine.execute(CommandLine.java:1864)\r\n\tat tech.pegasys.artemis.Artemis.main(Artemis.java:23)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nError message displayed indicating that the `config` directory must exist or the `--outputFile` option must be used. \r\n\r\nAlso, if the file already exists, the existing keys in the file are overwritten.  Not sure if this is the desired behaviour? ",
